          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>Yiddish</add>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <add>Yiddish</add>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <persName role="author">Nathan Ottinger</persName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>
                                        <sic>
                                                  <addressee>Rev Isak Leeser</addressee>
                                        </sic>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>Yiddish</add>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>, <date>Sunday,
                                                  11 Nissan (Apr.)</date></p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <date>1851</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">On <date>Friday</date> I received your letter
                                        along<lb/> with seven prayer-books, though your letter<lb/>
                                        arrived in the evening. At your request<lb/> I am sending
                                        you the money for the<lb/> books sold, namely $12â€”, since
                                        for<lb/> the previous two packages I had to pay<lb/> three
                                        shillings express charge for each,<lb/> and for this last
                                        one, four shillings. I<lb/> don't know why it should have
                                        cost<lb/> a shilling more this time. This makes 10<lb/>
                                        shillings and there is due me two shillings<lb/> which I
                                        shall deduct from the next<lb/> account. I still have in my
                                        possession<lb/> three Portuguese prayer books, two sets<lb/>
                                        of Pentateuchs and the last package. As<lb/> soon as I have
                                        sold it, I shall send you<lb/> what is due. With regard to
                                        the prayer<lb/> books, I am grateful to you. I have given
                                        50<lb/> copies to <persName>Mr. Sachs</persName>, of Sefat
                                        Emet prayer<lb/> books. I am still the <sic>possesor</sic>
                                        of the most<lb/> books of every kind, most of them of
                                        Por</p>
                              <pb n="4"/>
                              <p>tuguese, Polish and Ashkenazic ritual, in<lb/> excellent binding,
                                        large and small. I<lb/> also have bought up many
                                                  <del>of</del> Viennese books such as<lb/>
                                        Gemarrahs, Mishna, and pentateuchs, as<lb/> well as a
                                        Portuguese prayer book printed in<lb/>
                                        <placeName>Vienna</placeName>. I desire that you again
                                        mention this in<lb/> the "Occident". I also have a
                                        second-hand<lb/> Torah, and Tiphillin, Mezzuzot, Zizit,<lb/>
                                        Talithin, silk and woolen. I hope<lb/> you will soon let me
                                        know about the<lb/> receipt of the money.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Wishing you a happy holiday,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Your friend,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">
                                        <persName role="author">Nathan Ottinger</persName>
                              </p>
                    </body>
